North Korea pledged to dismantle the missile base and nuclear complex at a meeting with Moon this month if the United States takes "appropriate measures."
According to him, Kim claimed that the “corresponding measures” he sought were the security guarantees Trump promised in Singapore and a shift to normalize relations with Washington.
