Charles Czeisler, a professor of sleep medicine at Harvard Medical School, and Brigham City, a specialist in women's hospitals, have developed a course that he says is the first of its kind in the United States.
The inspiration for preparing this course came after a talk about the effects of lack of sleep on learning.
