The culture of pride not sleeping at night, according to him, still exists. Modern technologies and the increasing pressure on students have led to the problem of growing lack of sleep.
“To make sure you get enough and quality sleep, there should be a student’s secret weapon in combating stress, exhaustion and anxiety,” he said, “even avoiding weight gain because sleep deprivation switches the brain into starvation mode, so students are constantly hungry.”
Raymond So, a 19-year-old Californian who studies chemical and physical biology, helped Professor Czeisler prepare a course when he attended one of the subjects he taught at Harvard in his first year last year.
He said the course opened his eyes and inspired him to apply for a course available to the entire campus.
He hopes that the next step will be to invite all postgraduate students to listen to this course before starting to attend this competitive institution.
